        <h2 id="verdict">Is AIOSEO worth it in 2026? Final verdict</h2>
        <p><strong>For WordPress agencies and serious site owners: yes.</strong> Pro tier at $199/yr is the sweet spot — schema, local, redirects, WooCommerce SEO, and tier-one support all in one. The setup wizard alone saves an hour on every new client install.</p>

        <p><strong>For budget-sensitive owners: probably no.</strong> RankMath's free tier covers 85% of what AIOSEO Pro charges $199/yr for. Unless you specifically need AIOSEO's support tier or smart import, RankMath wins on value.</p>

        <p><strong>For owners who need content produced: no — wrong tool.</strong> AIOSEO does not write a word. It configures your CMS. You will still need writers, an optimization tool, and a publishing workflow. The total is $2,500–$5,000/mo before AIOSEO sees a single page rank.</p>

